I think one of the problem here is `StandardRepresentation#toStringOf(CompletableFuture<?> future)` that tries to call `join()` on the future. definitely bad.

I'm thinking that the current assertions check the future at at point in time and the error should represent the future at this same point in time, if that is not possible it should avoid to display the future state later on as it would not be relevant. 

@tkruse thoughts ?
